"title": "8210: commitment, to God's people",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8210: commitment, to god's people",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Commitment to God means a commitment to his people. Believers are meant to be nourished and supported by the church, and to work towards its edification.</p>\n<h2>Commitment to the church</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:42\">ACT 2:42</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:3-Eph4:4\">EPH 4:3–4:4</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:15\">COL 3:15</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:4-Rom12:10\">ROM 12:4–12:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:12-1Cor12:27\">1CO 12:12–12:27</a></p>\n<h2>Commitment to other Christians is an expression of love made known in Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:34-John13:35\">JHN 13:34–13:35</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:13-Col3:14\">COL 3:13–3:14</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:22\">1PE 1:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:12\">JHN 15:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:17\">JHN 15:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:10\">ROM 12:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:16\">ROM 12:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:8\">ROM 13:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:13\">GAL 5:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:32-Eph5:2\">EPH 4:32–5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess3:12\">1TH 3:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:9\">1TH 4:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:3\">2TH 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:1\">HEB 13:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:17\">1PE 2:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:11\">1JN 3:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:23\">1JN 3:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:7\">1JN 4:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:21\">1JN 4:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:2\">1JN 5:2</a></p>\n<h2>Such commitment is expressed in mutual responsibility and concern</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:2\">GAL 6:2</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:24-Heb10:25\">HEB 10:24–10:25</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:8\">1PE 3:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:13\">ROM 14:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:7\">ROM 15:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:14\">ROM 15:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:10\">1CO 1:10</a> <em>Paul's concern for unity among believers</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:21\">EPH 5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:13\">COL 3:13</a> <em>the responsibility of believers to forgive one another</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:16\">COL 3:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:11\">1TI 5:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:13\">HEB 3:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:11\">JAS 4:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:9\">1PE 4:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:5\">1PE 5:5</a></p>\n<h2>For its leaders, commitment to the church may prove a joy and a burden</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28\">ACT 20:28</a></strong> <em>Paul speaking to the elders of the church at Ephesus</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:28\">2CO 11:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:24\">COL 1:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:8\">1TH 2:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:12-1Thess5:13\">1TH 5:12–5:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:1\">1TI 3:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:17\">HEB 13:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:1-1Pet5:3\">1PE 5:1–5:3</a></p>",
